> Adjust racks to top and middle positions for 4 servings. Use 1 tsp Frank's Seasoning per step.

> TIP: If green beans are done before chicken, remove from sheet and continue roasting chicken.

> 4 SERVINGS: Use 2 TBSP butter (in first butter melting step) and 3 TBSP butter (in potatoes).

Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

In a #small bowl, combine half the @sour cream{4%tablespoon}(divided, half used here), ½ tsp
@Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{7.2%g} (you'll use the rest later), and a big pinch
of @salt{}. Stir in @water{} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

Place 1 TBSP @butter{3%tablespoon}(divided, 1 TBSP used here) in a #medium microwave-safe bowl;
microwave until melted, ~{30-45%seconds}.

Stir in @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup}, @monterey jack cheese{1/4%cup},
remaining Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning, and a big pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Dice @yukon gold potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Place in a #medium pot with enough salted
water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil; cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup
potato cooking liquid, then drain.

Add a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon} and scallion whites to empty #pot over low heat;
cook until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Return potatoes to pot; mash with remaining sour cream and 1 TBSP butter until smooth and
creamy, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with salt and pepper.
Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While potatoes cook, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over
with salt and pepper. Place on one side of a lightly oiled #baking sheet{}.

Mound tops of chicken with panko mixture, pressing firmly to adhere (no need to coat the undersides).

Toss @green beans{6%ounce} on opposite side of baking sheet from chicken with a large drizzle of
@olive oil{2%teaspoon} and a pinch of salt and pepper.

Roast on top rack until chicken is golden brown and cooked through and green beans are tender,
~{15-18%minutes}.

Transfer roasted green beans to a #large bowl; add 1 TBSP butter and toss until melted.

Divide green beans, potatoes, and chicken between plates. Drizzle chicken with creamy Buffalo sauce
and @honey{2%teaspoon} (or serve on the side for dipping). Garnish potatoes and chicken with
scallion greens and serve.